It appears that rust doesn&#39;t expose this functionality in the stdlib yet (as of 1.35.0). However, if you&#39;re using a normal Unix-like system and don&#39;t want an extra crates.io dependency, you can easily use the required system calls by linking to your system&#39;s c library via ffi: (note the lowercase &#39;c&#39; for the library name)

```
#[link(name=&quot;c&quot;)]
extern &quot;C&quot; {
    fn geteuid() -&gt; u32;
    fn getegid() -&gt; u32;
}
```

If you&#39;re using GNI/Linux in particular, you won&#39;t need to link to libc at all since the system call symbols are automatically made available to your program via the vdso. (in other word, just use a plain `extern` block without the link attribute).

